<ArrayOfModuleData>

  <!-- 1. Introduction -->
  <ModuleData>
    <Id>Introduction</Id>
    <CourseId>HV Battery</CourseId>
    <Anchor>
      <Type>Locator</Type>
      <LocatorId>Section 1</LocatorId>
    </Anchor>
    <LinkRootLocatorId>Section 1 Root</LinkRootLocatorId>
    
    <Concepts>
      <!-- Concept 1: High Voltage Battery -->
      <ConceptData>
        <Id>High Voltage Battery</Id>

        <Keywords>
          <KeywordData>
            <Keyword>High Voltage Battery</Keyword>
            <VirtualColor>Highlight</VirtualColor>
          </KeywordData>
          <KeywordData>
            <Keyword>Begin</Keyword>
            <VirtualColor>Highlight2</VirtualColor>
          </KeywordData>
        </Keywords>

        <Actions>

          <!-- Introduce High Voltage Battery -->

          <ActionData>
            <Delay>1</Delay>
            <Type>Introduce</Type>
            <Text>Today, I’d like to introduce you to the High Voltage Battery for Model 3.</Text>
            <Content>
              <Id>High Voltage Battery</Id>
              <Anchor>
                <ContentId>Model3</ContentId>
                <LocatorId>High Voltage Battery</LocatorId>
              </Anchor>
            </Content>
          </ActionData>

          <!-- End Introduce -->

          <ActionData>
            <Text>This course assumes prior knowledge of the Model S High Voltage Battery.</Text>
          </ActionData>
          <ActionData>
            <Text>If you would like to refresh your knowledge</Text>
          </ActionData>
          <ActionData>
            <Text>review the High Voltage Battery architecture for Model S course in Bridge</Text>
          </ActionData>

        </Actions>

        <!-- Unlock the cover -->

        <Assessments>
          <AssessmentData>
            <Collection>
              <Score>20</Score>
              <Title>Unlock Component</Title>
              <Prompt>Find all the bolts on the High Voltage Battery to remove the cover. When you're ready, select Begin.</Prompt>
              <ContentId>High Voltage Battery</ContentId>
              <LocatorIds>
                <string>Bolt 1</string>
                <string>Bolt 2</string>
                <string>Bolt 3</string>
                <string>Bolt 4</string>
              </LocatorIds>
            </Collection>
          </AssessmentData>
          <ActionData>
            <Type>Hide</Type>
            <Id>High Voltage Battery Cover</Id>
          </ActionData>
        </Assessments>
      </ConceptData>

      <!-- Concept 2: Penthouse -->
      <ConceptData>
        <Id>Penthouse</Id>

        <Keywords>
          <KeywordData>
            <Keyword>Penthouse</Keyword>
            <VirtualColor>Highlight</VirtualColor>
          </KeywordData>
          <KeywordData>
            <Keyword>DC DC Converter</Keyword>
            <VirtualColor>Highlight2</VirtualColor>
          </KeywordData>
          <KeywordData>
            <Keyword>High Voltage Junction Box</Keyword>
            <VirtualColor>Highlight3</VirtualColor>
          </KeywordData>
          <KeywordData>
            <Keyword>Charger</Keyword>
            <VirtualColor>Highlight4</VirtualColor>
          </KeywordData>
          <KeywordData>
            <Keyword>Front Junction Box</Keyword>
            <VirtualColor>Highlight5</VirtualColor>
          </KeywordData>
        </Keywords>

        <Actions>

          <ActionData>
            <Type>Hide</Type>
            <Content>
              <Id>Battery Assembly Shell</Id>
            </Content>
          </ActionData>
          
          <ActionData>
            <Type>Color</Type>
            <Delay>1</Delay>
            <VirtualColor>Disabled</VirtualColor>
            <Content>
              <Id>High Voltage Battery</Id>
            </Content>
          </ActionData>

          <ActionData>
            <Delay>1</Delay>
            <Text>The basic function of the High Voltage Battery in Model 3 has not changed from Model S and X.</Text>
          </ActionData>
          <ActionData>
            <Text>However, there are significant changes to the battery architecture.</Text>
          </ActionData>

          <ActionData>
            <Delay>0</Delay>
            <Type>Show</Type>
            <Content>
              <Id>Foreground</Id>
            </Content>
          </ActionData>
          
          <ActionData>
            <Type>Show</Type>
            <Content>
              <Id>PenthouseAnimation</Id>
              <Anchor>
                <Type>Locator</Type>
                <ContentId>Foreground</ContentId>
                <LocatorId>Billboard</LocatorId>
                <Scale>Identity</Scale>
                <Rotation>Identity</Rotation>
              </Anchor>
            </Content>
            <Wait>false</Wait>
          </ActionData>
                  
          <ActionData>
            <Text>For starters, the DC DC Converter, Charger, High Voltage Junction Box, and Front Junction Box are no longer independent components.</Text>
          </ActionData>
          <ActionData>
            <Type>Introduce</Type>
            <Text>In Model 3 they have been integrated into a new component on the battery, called the Penthouse.</Text>
            <Content>
              <Id>Penthouse</Id>
              <Anchor>
                <ContentId>High Voltage Battery</ContentId>
                <LocatorId>Penthouse</LocatorId>
              </Anchor>
            </Content>
          </ActionData>

          <ActionData>
            <Type>Hide</Type>
            <Content>
              <Id>PenthouseAnimation</Id>
            </Content>
          </ActionData>

          <ActionData>
            <Type>Hide</Type>
            <Content>
              <Id>Foreground</Id>
            </Content>
          </ActionData>

          <ActionData>
            <Delay>2.0</Delay>
          </ActionData>
          
        </Actions>
      </ConceptData>
 
      <!-- Concept 3: Rapid Swap -->
      <ConceptData>
        <Id>Rapid Swap</Id>

        <Keywords>
          <KeywordData>
            <Keyword>Rapid Splitter</Keyword>
            <VirtualColor>Highlight2</VirtualColor>
          </KeywordData>
          <KeywordData>
            <Keyword>Rapid Mate</Keyword>
            <VirtualColor>Highlight3</VirtualColor>
          </KeywordData>
          <KeywordData>
            <Keyword>Outside Elements</Keyword>
            <VirtualColor>Highlight4</VirtualColor>
          </KeywordData>
        </Keywords>

        <Actions>
          
          <ActionData>
            <Type>Color</Type>
            <VirtualColor>Disabled</VirtualColor>
            <Content>
              <Id>Penthouse</Id>
            </Content>
          </ActionData>
          
          <ActionData>
            <Text>Additionally, the Rapid Splitter and Rapid Mate are nowhere to be found on Model 3.</Text>
          </ActionData>
          <ActionData>
            <Text>This is exciting as it means better reliability for Model 3 compared to Model S and X.</Text>
          </ActionData>
          <ActionData>
            <Text>You may be realizing that this also means that the battery cannot be rapidly swapped.</Text>
          </ActionData>
          <ActionData>
            <Text>Not to worry!</Text>
          </ActionData>
          <ActionData>
            <Text>Although the battery for Model 3 takes a bit longer to drop</Text>
          </ActionData>
          <ActionData>
            <Text>other design changes have been made so that you don’t have to drop it as frequently as S and X to replace components.</Text>
          </ActionData>
          <ActionData>
            <Text>Finally</Text>
          </ActionData>
          <ActionData>
            <Text>a lot of effort has gone into making the Model 3 High Voltage Battery more resistant to Outside Elements such as water</Text>
          </ActionData>
      
          <ActionData>
            <Type>Clear</Type>
          </ActionData>
        </Actions>

        <Assessments>
          <AssessmentData>
            <MultipleChoice>
              <Score>15</Score>
              <Title>Pop Quiz!</Title>
              <Prompt>What is new on Model 3?</Prompt>
              <Correct>
                <int>0</int>
              </Correct>
              <Options>
                <ButtonData>
                  <Caption>Penthouse</Caption>
                </ButtonData>
                <ButtonData>
                  <Caption>Rapid Splitter</Caption>
                </ButtonData>
                <ButtonData>
                  <Caption>High Voltage Junction Box</Caption>
                </ButtonData>
              </Options>
            </MultipleChoice>
          </AssessmentData>
        </Assessments>
        
      </ConceptData>
    </Concepts>
  </ModuleData>

</ArrayOfModuleData>